        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 1:58PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 158 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles east of Cass, or 15 miles northeast of Ozark, moving southeast
at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Woodland...                       Oak Grove in Johnson County...
Hunt...                           Catalpa...
Wolf Pen Campground...            Harmony...
Yale...                           Friley...
Ozone...                          Hillcrest in Johnson County...
Oark...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
